#: ../../../reference/sitemaps.rst:2
msgid "Sitemap support"
msgstr ""

#: ../../../reference/sitemaps.rst:4
msgid ""
"`Sitemaps <https://www.sitemaps.org/>`__ allow you to inform search engines "
"about URLs that are available for crawling. This makes your content more :"
"term:`discoverable <discoverability>`, and improves your :doc:`Search Engine "
"Optimization (SEO) </guides/technical-docs-seo-guide>`."
msgstr ""

#: ../../../reference/sitemaps.rst:9
msgid "How it works"
msgstr ""

#: ../../../reference/sitemaps.rst:11
msgid ""
"The ``sitemap.xml`` file is read by search engines to index your "
"documentation. It contains information such as:"
msgstr ""

#: ../../../reference/sitemaps.rst:14
msgid "When a URL was last updated."
msgstr ""

#: ../../../reference/sitemaps.rst:15
msgid "How often that URL changes."
msgstr ""

#: ../../../reference/sitemaps.rst:16
msgid "How important this URL is in relation to other URLs on the site."
msgstr ""

#: ../../../reference/sitemaps.rst:17
msgid "What translations are available for a page."
msgstr ""

#: ../../../reference/sitemaps.rst:19
msgid ""
"Read the Docs automatically generates a ``sitemap.xml`` for your project. "
"The sitemap includes :ref:`public and not hidden versions <versions:Version "
"states>` of your documentation and when they were last updated, sorted by "
"version number."
msgstr ""

#: ../../../reference/sitemaps.rst:23
msgid ""
"This allows search engines to prioritize results based on the version "
"number, sorted by `semantic versioning`_."
msgstr ""

#: ../../../reference/sitemaps.rst:27
msgid "Custom ``sitemap.xml``"
msgstr ""

#: ../../../reference/sitemaps.rst:29
msgid ""
"You can provide a custom ``sitemap.xml`` file with your docs build output. "
"Read the Docs looks for this file in the **default version** of your "
"project, because ``sitemap.xml`` is served from the root of your docs domain."
msgstr ""

#: ../../../reference/sitemaps.rst:33
msgid ""
"If this custom file exists, it is served as-is. If it does not exist, Read "
"the Docs serves the generated sitemap instead."
msgstr ""

#: ../../../reference/sitemaps.rst:36
msgid ""
"You can also point crawlers to a different sitemap URL via ``robots.txt``. "
"See :doc:`/reference/robots` for details."
msgstr ""

#: ../../../reference/sitemaps.rst:39
msgid "For example, in ``robots.txt``::"
msgstr ""

#: ../../../reference/sitemaps.rst:41
msgid ""
"User-agent: *\n"
"Allow: /\n"
"\n"
"Sitemap: https://docs.example.com/en/stable/sitemap.xml"
msgstr ""
